@node "Just_A_Little_Story" "Just A Little Story..."
@next "Lyrics"
@prev "Main"

                            @{b}JUST A LITTLE STORY...@{ub}
                            @{fg shine}~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{fg text}


It was Spring 1996ad. Pera, Alex, BMK and I were at the Euromercato mall I
don't remember for doing what. We just got off the car and Alex told me:
"I've got the idea for The Intel Outside sequel. We could use another
@{"TI.PI.CAL." link "Copyright" 0}'s song...". I said: "No, I don't want to use another TI.PI.CAL.'s
track; it seems to me like a forcing.". Alex: "No, listen. Do you know @{i}It
Hurts@{ui}? Well... PC hurts, PC hurts, PC hurts... when it woooorkss...".

               AH, AH, AH, AH, AH!!!  \8^0  (general laugh)

I said: "Great idea! We will make it!".
A lot of water is passed under the bridges since then, but we finnaly made
it. To be precise the module was ready for the beginning of October 1997ad, in
fact I presented it at the exhibition @{b}Pianeta Amiga@{ub} (20/21-Sep-1997ad
Empoli, ITALY), but I wanted to add also some bonus files like in @{i}The Intel
Outside@{ui}: the pseudo-cover took many time to be accomplished because I needed
something/someone to digitize ourselves (I found a Mac user friend of mine
who bought a scanner in December only).

This song, as you'll may listen, is dedicated to those guys that left the
Amiga for joining the Pee Cee side (how many troubles with their
ultra-pumped @{i}dream@{ui} machines(?!)).

Ok, that's all. Check out the @{"credits" link "Credits" 0} and @{"lyrics" link "Lyrics" 0}, but before this I want to
let you know more two little things:
1. This is not a Pure Amiga Product like @{i}The Intel Outside@{ui} module, because
   I used a Mac for scanning our images.
2. @{"TI.PI.CAL." link "Copyright" 0}'s track It Hurts is a cover: the original song was written
   by Lotus Eaters about in 1984-1985 (thanks to Jon Bat for this note).
@endnode

