                                @{b}CREDITS@{ub}
                                @{fg shine}~~~~~~~@{fg text}

                             @{fg fill}IDEA@{fg text}  Neil Martin (formally Alex Michieli)
                           @{fg fill}LYRICS@{fg text}  Neil Martin, OgniX
                @{fg fill}TRACKER COMPOSING@{fg text}  Pera, OgniX, Jon Bat
                           @{fg fill}VOCALS@{fg text}  Jon Bat
                   @{fg fill}ORIGINAL TRACK@{fg text}  @{"It Hurts - TI.PI.CAL." link "Copyright" 0} ©


PC Hurts has been made on an Amiga 4000  KS 3.1 - WB 3.1 - 18 MB RAM
(2 MB Chip RAM + 16 MB Fast RAM -> useless but...  :)  , but it could be
made also on my (OgniX) other Amiga, a 500 with KS 2.0 - WB 2.1 - ECS - 4 MB
RAM (2 MB Chip RAM + 2 MB Fast): next time, when I compose a new module,
I'll use this last one.

Music tracker program used: OctaMED V5.04 (OctaMED Sound Studio
V1.03c is available for free at the RBF Software WWW site
-> http://www.octamed.co.uk ).

Jon Bat vocals have been recorded mainly at Bruno's
studio (previously called 21 Sound Studio); later, due to errors, a couple
of phrases have been re-recorded at Viva Radio.

Recording equipment: AKG Microphone, Sony DCT-60 DAT Deck and
Tascam DA-20 DAT Deck.

The sampling has been made with a Toccata audio board together
with the program Samplitude MS V2.10 (which has a bug in the IFF
8SVX saving function; however we loaded the samples as Raw files in
OctaMED).

The sad PC user drawn in the pseudo-cover has been inspired
by an advertising on an old number of Commodore Computer Club... was
a famous italian magazine for Commodore users (VIC-20, C-64, C-128,
C-16, etc.).
Coordinates - CCC N°38 page 5 "Il vero linguaggio macchina del
Commodore 64"


