@node "System_Req." "System Requirements"
@next "Distribution"
@prev "Credits"

                           @{b}SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS@{ub}
                           @{fg shine}~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{fg text}

 Due to use of a lot of samples, this MED module (OctaMED Pro V5.0 - MMD1)
 can be played only on Amigas with at least 2 MB of Chip RAM (ECS Agnus 8375
 or AGA) or on machines with 2 MB of RAM at least, if you use a player that
 loads samples in Fast RAM (eg. DeliTracker).

 Note: if you have a bare 2 MB Amiga, you may encounter some loading
       problems due to memory limitations.
       If you find these ones please try to reduce the amount of memory used
       by deactivating background programs (like commodities) and by
       reducing your Workbench colors and resolution.
       If you still have problems do the following:

    1. disable booting with Startup-Sequence by selecting the relative
       option in the bootup menu (press both mouse buttons after a reset
       for Amiga OS 2.0 and above) or by pressing <CTRL-D> to stop execution
       (Amiga OS 1.X).
    2. Once in the CLI type the complete path of the player followed by
       the complete path of the module, and than press <RETURN>.

       e.g.   DH0:Tools/OctaMEDPlayer DH0:Modules/PC_Hurts.med

    3. Pump up the volume and enjoy!    \;^)
@endnode

